parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive frame flex and suspension failure can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to loss of control, wheel separation, and damage to surrounding structures.
symptoms: Squeaky floors
furniture rubbing against walls
stairs rubbing against doors
excessive creaking noises while towing
wheel and tire loss
suspension failure
broken springs
sheared lug bolts
and damaged rotors and brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of undersized axles and suspension systems can lead to premature failure, accidents, and injuries, particularly in heavy RVs.
symptoms: Suspension failure
wheel and tire loss
broken springs
sheared lug bolts
and damaged rotors and brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Manufacturer Response and Warranty Coverage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate response from manufacturers and limited warranty coverage can leave owners with unsafe and defective vehicles, potentially leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Denied warranty claims
lack of assistance from manufacturers
and limited warranty coverage for certain models and owners.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame Failure and Structural Integrity Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frame can cause the separation of outside and inside body parts, leading to a loss of structural integrity, which can result in accidents or injuries while traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The outside and inside body parts start to separate
the 5th wheel can break free from the tow vehicle while traveling
screws fall out
decals get ruined
furniture or stairs rub against the walls
molding becomes twisted
and the roof may pop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Storage Door Failure Due to Design Flaws
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The storage doors can come open while towing, causing a hazard on the road and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Storage doors come open while towing
despite being shut and locked before departing
allowing slipstream to enter the gap and putting strain on the retaining locks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The catastrophic failure of the ABS brake system can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a complete loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes overheat
the brakes fail to slow the vehicle
the brakes produce a loud grinding or screeching noise
the brake drums turn red hot
the landing gear falls out of the assemblies
the brakes experience metal-on-metal contact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The systemic defect in the ABS brake system can cause widespread brake failures, putting numerous lives at risk, especially during travel seasons.
symptoms: Repeated brake failures
brake overheating
loss of braking ability
loud grinding or screeching noises
brake drums turning red hot
landing gear falling out of assemblies
metal-on-metal contact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate response from the manufacturer can lead to a lack of accountability, failure to address the root cause of the problem, and continued risk to customers' lives.
symptoms: Denial of widespread safety concerns
lack of acknowledgment of similar complaints from multiple owners
inadequate solutions or repairs
continued production and sale of defective vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause the engine to seize or fail, leading to costly repairs or even accidents.
symptoms: Oil droplets or puddles are seen under the vehicle
the oil level is consistently low
the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations
the engine warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle leaves an oil trail on the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the fuel pump makes unusual noises or vibrations
the fuel pump warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle has difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Thermal Events
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a thermal event, leading to a fire that can spread quickly and consume the RV, posing a significant risk to the occupants' safety and potentially causing fatalities.
symptoms: Unexplained electrical fires or thermal events in the generator compartment
smoke or burning smell
damage to the electrical system or surrounding components.
